      <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-primary-600 bg-primary-50 px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Guides</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 ml-3">Updated June 2026</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">All Bill Payment Methods in Pakistan — 2026 Complete Guide</h1>

    <p class="text-neutral-600 text-lg mb-4">Pakistan's bill payment ecosystem has transformed dramatically in the last decade. From standing in long queues at WAPDA offices or post offices, consumers now have <strong>9+ different payment channels</strong> — from mobile wallets and banking apps to ATMs and corner shops. But with so many options, it can be confusing to know which method is best for your situation. Should you pay through JazzCash or your bank app? Is a 1Bill shop cheaper than a bank branch? What if you don't have a bank account? This guide compares every payment method available in Pakistan — covering fees, processing times, pros and cons — so you can pick the best option for each bill.</p>

    <div class="bg-primary-50 border-l-4 border-primary-600 p-4 rounded-lg mb-8">
      <p class="font-semibold text-primary-800">Quick Summary: For most consumers, <strong>JazzCash or EasyPaisa</strong> is the best bill payment method — free, instant, works on any phone. For larger bills, use your bank's mobile app. For cash payments without a bank account, use 1Bill shops (Rs. 30–50 fee) or utility customer service centers (free).</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Comparison Table: All Bill Payment Methods</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg">
        <thead class="bg-neutral-100">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Method</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Fee</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Speed</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Bank Account?</th>
            <th class="text-left p-3 border-b border-neutral-200">Best For</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-200">
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">JazzCash</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">Quick everyday payments</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">EasyPaisa</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">Telenor users</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Bank mobile app</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">Yes</td><td class="p-3">Large bills</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">ATM</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">Yes</td><td class="p-3">After-hours payment</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Bank branch</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">4 hours</td><td class="p-3">No (cash)</td><td class="p-3">Cash payments</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">1Bill shop</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30–50</td><td class="p-3">12–24h</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">No bank account</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">NADRA e-Sahulat</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 30</td><td class="p-3">24–48h</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">Remote areas</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Post office</td><td class="p-3">Rs. 20</td><td class="p-3">2–3 days</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">Small towns</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Utility CSC</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">No</td><td class="p-3">Disputes, instant reflect</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="p-3 font-semibold">Credit card (website)</td><td class="p-3">Free</td><td class="p-3">Instant</td><td class="p-3">Yes</td><td class="p-3">Reward points</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
